SIMPLE: non_obstante
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Non obstante
<hw>Non` ob*stan"te</hw> <pr>(n⟦ocr⟧n` ⟦ocr⟧b*st⟦acr⟧n"t⟦esl⟧)</pr>.
<ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Notwithstanding; in opposition to, or
in spite of, what has been stated, or is to be stated or
admitted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A clause in old English statutes
and letters patent, importing a license from the crown to do a thing
notwithstanding any statute to the contrary. This dispensing power was
abolished by the Bill of Rights.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In this very reign [Henry III.] the practice of dispensing with
statutes by a <qex>non obstante</qex> was introduced.</q>
<rj><qau>Hallam.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Non obstante veredicto</b></col> <ety>[LL.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a judgment sometimes entered by order of the
court, for the plaintiff, <xlati>notwithstanding a verdict</xlati> for
the defendant.</cd> <rj><au>Stephen.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonoic</ent>⟦br⟧
